cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SOC, cs.NI, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of selecting a minimum size subset of nodes in a network that allows to activate all the nodes of the network. This problem is related to social influence, network analysis, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents a fast and simple algorithm that produces solutions that outperform the ones obtained by using the best algorithms in the literature, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The theoretical analysis of the algorithm's performance suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the experiments show that the performance of the algorithms correlates with the modularity of the analyzed network, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
